# Absolute API origin (no trailing slash). Required for device/simulator
# (Metro cannot use the Vite web proxy).
#
# Pick the host that the *device* can reach — not always 127.0.0.1:
#   iOS Simulator:     http://127.0.0.1:4004
#   Android emulator:  http://10.0.2.2:4004
#   Physical phone:    http://<your-lan-ip>:4004   (e.g. http://192.168.1.152:4004)
#   Hosted:            https://baykus.xava.me
#
# Server must be running (`pnpm dev` → :4004). "Network request failed" usually
# means wrong host or the API process is down.
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=

# Google OAuth (multi mode). Server must list these in BAYKUS_GOOGLE_CLIENT_IDS:
# first ID = web (exposed via session.oauthProviders); later = iOS/Android accept-audiences (014 E122).
# Expo Go can fall back to the session web client ID when native IDs are unset.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_WEB_CLIENT_ID=
# EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_IOS_CLIENT_ID=
# EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_ANDROID_CLIENT_ID=

# Apple Sign-In (iOS): enable Sign In with Apple on the App ID matching
# me.xava.baykus. Append the App ID / Services ID as non-first entries in
# BAYKUS_APPLE_CLIENT_IDS (first ID remains the web Services ID for the SPA).
